14/05/2007
TIRANA, Albania -- Edi Rama was re-elected as leader of the main opposition Socialist Party (SP) in an internal referendum on Saturday (May 12th). A total of 80,000 SP members in Albania and around 2,800 in Greece and Italy had the right to participate in the voting. Rama won 97.5% of the votes. SP members also elected chairmen of the municipal SP organisations and delegates to the general SP congress, which takes place later this month. (A1 TV, Top-Channel, Kohajone, Telegrafi, VOA - 13/05/07)
